homedescription: On the quaint island of Alameda, across the Bay from San Francisco, lies this bright, spacious three story home with a spectacular robust garden and access to the water. The largest property and standalone townhouse in Ballen Bay, this four bedroom, three and a half bath home is bathed in natural light. Large deck off the kitchen and family room leads to a brick-paved yard complete with poplar, palms, multiple producing fruit trees such as plum, mulberry, pomegranate, apricot and lemon, as well as grape vines and many rose bushes.The commute to San Francisco is a relaxing trip on the nearby ferry or a quick 20 minute drive. Close to major freeways, yet quiet. Alameda is a tranquil island environment that has so much to offer. Many parks and public activities abound. Alameda has a true community feel with great schools.

CULTURE

LOCAL COMMUNITY

Spacious Waterfront Living!

Waterfront living at its finest in the heart of San Francisco's vibrant Mission Bay neighborhood. Stunning and spacious, this rarely available two-story loft style residence showcases over 1,600 square feet of living spaces, 2 large bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, grand living and dining spaces with soaring 11-foot ceilings, chef's kitchen, formal dining space, 2 private patios, and gorgeous Brazilian cherry hardwood flooring. homedescription: "Incredibly Stunning” is a solid descriptor for 175 Bluxome Street in Mission Bay. Simple, modern design attracts a diverse group of residents who can appreciate live/work dwellings. Converted in 2005 to condominiums by Emerald Fund, 175 Bluxome is a true loft building and offers proper downtown living by San Francisco-based Mark Horton Architecture. Located off the building’s tranquil courtyard and near the water feature and mature plantings, this loft boasts soaring ceilings and a contemporary interior. The living space has great volume with soaring ceilings and double-high windows overlooking Bluxome Street. The remodeled kitchen comes complete with stainless steel appliances and granite countertops. New carpet in the bedroom and new paint are recent upgrades. A den area is perfect for a guest bedroom, media room, office, or library. Add to that choice features such as hardwood floors, in-unit laundry, and 1-car parking with additional storage. Current HOA dues are $353.32 per month. homedescription: 464 Collingwood is a lovely 1947 Art Deco condo on two levels, in an immaculate two unit building. Entering through custom metal gate and up one flight of terrazzo steps, you enter into a foyer with gorgeous hardwood floors. The bedrooms are located on opposite ends of the home for ultimate privacy. A lovely full bath completes the main level. An additional 585 square feet (per Floor Plan Visuals drawing) of deeded lower level flex space with half bath provides it`s next owner with a multitude of opportunities. This floor has direct access to gardens and decks also with Westerly views to Twin Peaks. Quiet, architecturally significant and located on a desirable Eureka Valley block, this home is in striking distance of the cafes and shops of the Castro and Noe Valley. There is Independent garage parking for one car with potential guest parking in the driveway. A real gem not to be missed!Please visit: www.464Collingwood.com

homedescription:
AT THE CORNER OF COMFORT AND ELEGANCE

Lovely and classic, this 1918 Craftsman home in Upper Lakeshore has a quiet calm and tons of charm. Located where Piedmont and Crocker Highlands intersect, the street has an open feel and gets lots of light. The front yard and architectural details give this house a solid street presence. 

From inside the foyer looking at the living room, you can appreciate the beautiful hardwood floors, the coved ceilings and period built-ins on either side of the marble-tiled fireplace. The Craftsman style grid windows frame a pretty view of greenery.

The dining room, too, has beautiful tree-filled outlooks and has an open floor plan that leads gracefully into the kitchen, with a butcher-block counter/bar bridging the two rooms. A stainless steel sink and appliances and maize quartz countertops bring lots of style and function. At the back of the kitchen is a laundry nook and lots of storage. The dramatic French doors with a palladium arch lead to a level-out backyard of lush terraced gardens, paved outdoor dining spaces, a built-in grill, a fire pit and abundant space for playing and entertaining for all ages. A long driveway provides plenty of off-street parking.

Two bedrooms and a full bathroom complete the downstairs. Upstairs is another bedroom with an angled ceiling and giant swing-in casement windows. The master bedroom is spacious and bright; soaring ceilings and high windows capture views of the sky, all the windows frame exceptionally pretty garden views. Through sliding glass doors a deck and outside staircase gives access to the the yard. The bath is like a spa: skylights, mosaic tiles, a large soaking tub and a fancy glassed-in shower with two swing-arm shower heads offer plenty of luxury. A bonus small office/sitting room is an ideal reading nook, art studio or play space.  

The vibrant Lakeshore shopping district beckons close by with Peet's Coffee, Starbucks, Trader Joe's, the Farmer's Market, the Grand Lake Theater and some of Oakland's best restaurants all within easy walking distance. This historic area is also minutes from Lake Merritt and affords easy accessibility to San Francisco by car or public transportation.  

This gracious home is the perfect place to come home to and unwind, an urban oasis with lots of appeal.

homedescription:
SOMETHING FOR EVERYONE

From the street, it is a handsome Prairie Style, traditional and stately, with English Yews on either side of a large, multi-lite beveled glass door. Once inside, from the level-in entrance, one can appreciate the architectural details of stepped ceilings, crown moldings, hardwood floors and period built-ins in both the living room and the dining room. The large living room has a gorgeous tiled Craftsman fireplace as a focal point; both rooms have lovely tree-filled outlooks from the front.

Moving through the swing door in the dining room, the kitchen and breakfast nook are sunny and bright, with fantastic hill views from all the windows. Granite counters, pantry built-ins, a wine refrigerator and a convenient powder room make this room a great place to create meals and memories.

Upstairs are three bedrooms and a bonus sunroom/office space with more fabulous views of both the hills, including Mount Tamalpais, and the scenic back yard. A spacious bathroom has wonderful 1920s details: original porcelain fixtures and huge stand alone shower with beautiful vintage tile. The master bedroom has a lovely archway leading to a sitting area and the en suite bathroom, which also has a period feel. At twilight, spectacular sunsets fill the windows from many vantage points.

On the lower floor, another surprise - a bonus independent au pair/in-law apartment downstairs with separate entrance is a whole other world - a bedroom, living room, kitchen, dining area and bathroom, beautifully designed and with lots of storage. This level opens out onto the yard, making indoor/outdoor entertaining even easier.

The backyard is a marvel, it begins with a tiered brick patio overlooking a huge, level grassy play yard. This yard is exceptional in so many ways besides its size; it has lovely landscaping, including citrus and peach trees, a dawn redwood, giant impatiens, jasmine and sage; a garden shed in the corner and at the bottom of the bricked steps is a gate accessing Walavista Avenue. This yard is ideal for barbecues and other get-togethers to enjoy the temperate climate of Crocker Highlands.

This wonderfully-situated home is just a few blocks to the shops in the vibrant Lakeshore District, home to the well-loved and acclaimed Farmer's Market, many of Oakland's best restaurants, (both fine and casual), and family-friendly parks, all within easy walking distance. This historic area is also minutes from Lake Merritt and affords easy accessibility to San Francisco by car or public transportation.  

This is a home to discover and enjoy in so many ways, not the least of which its comfort, charm and style.
whatownerloves: Just blocks from the Lakeshore and Grand Avenue Shops, Grand Lake Farmers Market, carpool and express bus to SF.

homedescription:
Dazzling four bedroom, two bathroom Mediterranean home sits in an ideal location, and features light filled living spaces, an open layout, timelessly elegant period details, updated kitchen & bathrooms, as well as usable backyard space & one-car garage. Located in the Glenview Elementary School District, walking distance to Redwood Day School, multiple parks, and easy access to Park Boulevard shopping & amenities.

With magnanimous curb appeal, and a welcoming foyer, this home is immediately & infinitely inspiring. Upon entering through the grand arched wooden doorway, the open layout and vaulted ceilings, combined with exposed beams, and a warm color palate, together invite a sense of tranquility and refinement. Timeless Mediterranean architectural details meet the eye at every turn: from the grandiose bay window, original restored oak flooring, and crystal doorknobs, to the arced staircase, and wrought iron balustrade & handrail. The flow & feel of this home is exquisite, and it was updated with practical modern family living in mind.

The eat-in kitchen and adjacent formal dining area were designed with the chef & entertainer in mind: with stainless steel appliances, gas range, custom wood cabinetry, and plenty of storage. The kitchen also features unique detailed terra cotta tiled flooring, granite countertops, and oiled bronze sink & cabinet hardware. Light filters through every window, creating an airy, inviting, and serene ambiance. 

Upstairs are three generous bedrooms with large closets, and a handsomely updated bathroom with a hallway linen closet. The bathroom features subway tiles, glass hex tile flooring, and new fixtures. Downstairs features the second bathroom, laundry room, basement storage area, and connecting garage; as well as a large fourth bedroom with built-in shelving & French doors that open out to the bright & spacious landscaped backyard.

homedescription:
HOUSE BEAUTIFUL

This is how they used to make houses: large rooms, beautiful architectural details, comfort and style existing effortlessly together. The bold silhouette of this 1919 Prairie-style Craftsman is softened by lush landscaping of jasmine, rosemary, abutilon, salvia and vines of Thompson grapes. A large porch welcomes in a classic manner.

The living room is large and light-filled, with a stone fireplace bracketed by bookshelves. Giant picture windows frame views of the hills. Wainscoting, crown molding and handsome oak floors bring yet more elegance. 

The formal dining room is big and bright, with windows overlooking the garden. The convivial, airy open floor plan brings the kitchen and dining room together, separated by a low kitchen bar. The kitchen is the heart of the home, and this one is all charm. Sleek veined quartz counters, a subway tile back splash, stainless steel appliances, maple floors and a cheerful view from oversized steel casement windows make this an especially appealing place to cook, entertain friends or hang out with the family. A powder room and guest room off the kitchen overlooks the garden.

Outside, the tiered garden is thoughtfully designed with lime, lemon, grapefruit and blood orange trees; fountain grass, herbs, roses and other drought-tolerant plants fill the raised beds. A deck and studio shed, the "Little House,"  is a lovely locale to both entertain and to get away. 

Upstairs are three sizeable bedrooms, two of which overlook the garden, one has a calm sun room with tree-filled outlooks, all have nice walk-in closets. A hall bathroom has a vintage penny-tile floor and pedestal sink, and a built-in linen cabinet in the hallway is a nice period detail. The master bedroom has banks of windows capturing the light and views.

A fabulous location in the vibrant Lakeshore/Grand Lake neighborhood is another highlight of this home, with every need within walking distance: the Farmer's Market, grocery and hardware stores, in addition to the Lakeshore shopping district and some of Oakland's best restaurants. This historic area is also minutes from Lake Merritt and affords easy accessibility to San Francisco by car or public transportation.  

Spacious and gracious, this is a classic beauty, a great place to call home.

homedescription:
Of course you can make me sell it for the right price, as retirement is upon us. Downtown Santa Clara County Assessor's Parcel Number (APN): 120-30-045. 

Imagine if you will how much the units could rent for if one were to upgrade a little, furnish them and lease them to businesses that have employees traveling here or need temporary relocation. Probably 3,500 - 4,000 per unit/month cash flow. That's about 16,000 per month.  Now go do your mortgage math and you can see why downtown Palo Alto is such a value to own. More can be done with this lot. This is one of the bigger lots on Alma where there are both business and homes on the same block in the SOFA (South Of Forest Area). Close to public transportation and walking distance to Palo Alto high school downtown university ave., town and country shopping center, Palo Alto Medical Foundation, Stanford.

This is a single story 4 plex apartment building on a large lot. Bigger could be built today. It has multiple street address, perhaps originally planned to be converted to condos.  These four 1 BD 1BA units have rents under market. In downtown Palo Alto edge of SOFA, far enough away from train station that you don't hear the train breaks stopping. Separate laundry room. Separate storage.  Additional 120sq ft artist studio behind one of the units. All rents currently well under market with long time tenants now on month-to-month rents.  Look at the lot map photo, two lots behind it 35 & 36 or on the side 47 & 46. This is bigger than those put together and those homes will easily sell for 3-3.5M each today. 

You would be surprised how much money this downtown Palo Alto corner produces in cash flow today. I select tenants with monthly incomes and high credit scores such that paying the rent is no big deal. In exchange, I have little to do and keep the rents low.
whatownerloves: It has multiple street addresses. 1061 Alma as well as  103, 105 & 107 Lincoln Ave. It's well kept. Can be rented while you plan new buildings on this lot. Tenants are great people, please do not disturb. We enjoy owning this place.

homedescription: "Incredibly Stunning” is a solid descriptor for 175 Bluxome Street in Mission Bay. Simple, modern design attracts a diverse group of residents who can appreciate live/work dwellings. Converted in 2005 to condominiums by Emerald Fund, 175 Bluxome is a true loft building and offers proper downtown living by San Francisco-based Mark Horton Architecture.
